We just made the tapanad to go with a piece of marlin we grilled. It was perfect. I did use the anchovies, and it really adds a nice depth without making it taste "fishy." Didn't have red pepper, so used sun dried tomatoes, which I think work even better. The idea of including some fresh tomatoes is also intriguing. Will try that next time.

Rating: 3
This was easy to prepare & delicious. I actually had a huge jar of Paisana olive & roasted pepper mix, which provided most of ingredients for the relish, except that I had to pit all of the olives. I left out the anchovies & the topping was piquant enough with the remaining ingredients. Served this with cauliflower leek puree, since we eat low-carb. Speaking of which, this is a great low-carb dish!

