this was good, but I think I used olives that were too strong. I had only oil cured kalamatas which have a VERY strong taste and they overpowered the fish a little. I also used balsalmic not red wine vinegar which has a stronger taste. I tossed in some tomatoes as I had some "grape" cherry tomatoes about to go bad, and they were delicious. Served with couscous and asparagus. I used the left over olive relish, asparagus and couscous to make a salad inspired by TOMATO, BASIL AND COUSCOUS SALAD (on epicurious) and it was delicious as well.

